quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  11,84,"And to the people of Midian We sent their brother Shu’aib. He said, “O my people! Worship God. You have no god other than Him. And do not give short measure and weight. I do see you in prosperity now, but I truly fear for you the torment of an overwhelming Day"
  11,85,"O my people! Give full measure and weigh with justice. Do not defraud people of their property, nor go about spreading corruption in the land"
  11,86,What is left ˹as a lawful gain˺ by God is far better for you if you are ˹truly˺ believers. And I am not a keeper over you.”
  11,87,"They asked ˹sarcastically˺, “O Shu’aib! Does your prayer command you that we should abandon what our forefathers worshipped or give up managing our wealth as we please? Indeed, you are such a tolerant, sensible man!”"
  11,88,"He said, “O my people! Consider if I stand on a clear proof from my Lord and He has blessed me with a good provision from Him. I do not want to do what I am forbidding you from. I only intend reform to the best of my ability. My success comes only through God. In Him I trust and to Him I turn"
  11,89,"O my people! Do not let your opposition to me lead you to a fate similar to that of the people of Noah, or Hûd, or Ṣâliḥ. And the people of Lot are not far from you"
  11,90,"So seek your Lord’s forgiveness and turn to Him in repentance. Surely my Lord is Most Merciful, All-Loving.”"
  11,91,"They threatened, “O Shu’aib! We do not comprehend much of what you say, and surely we see you powerless among us. Were it not for your clan, we would have certainly stoned you, for you are nothing to us.”"
  11,92,"He said, “O my people! Do you have more regard for my clan than for God, turning your back on Him entirely? Surely my Lord is Fully Aware of what you do"
  11,93,"O my people! Persist in your ways, for I ˹too˺ will persist in mine. You will soon come to know who will be visited by a humiliating torment and is a liar! And watch! I too am watching with you!”"
  11,94,"When Our command came, We saved Shu’aib and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us. And the ˹mighty˺ blast overtook the wrongdoers, so they fell lifeless in their homes"
  11,95,as if they had never lived there. So away with Midian as it was with Thamûd
  11,96,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs and compelling proof"
  11,97,"to Pharaoh and his chiefs, but they followed the command of Pharaoh, and Pharaoh’s command was not well guided"
  11,98,He will be before his people on the Day of Judgment and will lead them into the Fire. What an evil place to be led into
  11,99,They were followed by a curse in this ˹life˺ and ˹will receive another˺ on the Day of Judgment. What an evil gift to receive
  11,100,"These are accounts, We relate to you ˹O Prophet˺, of the ˹destroyed˺ cities. Some are still standing ˹barren˺, while others have been mowed down"
  11,101,"We did not wrong them, rather they wronged themselves. The gods they invoked beside God were of no help at all when the command of your Lord came, and only contributed to their ruin"
  11,102,"Such is the ˹crushing˺ grip of your Lord when He seizes the societies entrenched in wrongdoing. Indeed, His grip is ˹terribly˺ painful and severe"
  11,103,Surely in this is a sign for those who fear the torment of the Hereafter. That is a Day for which humanity will be gathered and a Day ˹that will be˺ witnessed ˹by all˺
  11,104,We only delay it for a fixed term
  11,105,"When that Day arrives, no one will dare speak except with His permission. Some of them will be miserable, others joyful"
  11,106,"As for those bound for misery, they will be in the Fire, where they will be sighing and gasping"
  11,107,"staying there forever, as long as the heavens and the earth will endure, except what your Lord wills. Surely your Lord does what He intends"